Answer this question with the single letter for the correct answer only. A game of Plinko is played by dropping a ball at the top-middle of a set of pegs. Each time the ball hits a peg, it has a $\frac{1}{2}$ probability of deflecting either to the left or to the right. What is the probability that the ball lands in the middle slot as shown in the diagram (the red line)? [asy]
size(3inch, 2.25inch);
for (int i = 0; i < 8; i += 2) {

draw(circle((0, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((2, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((4, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((6, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((8, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((10, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((12, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((14, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((16, i + 1), 0.1));

draw(circle((1, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((3, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((5, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((7, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((9, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((11, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((13, i), 0.1));

draw(circle((15, i), 0.1));
}

pen target = red + linewidth(2);

draw((-0.8, -1)--(0.8, -1));
draw((1.2, -1)--(2.8, -1));
draw((3.2, -1)--(4.8, -1));
draw((5.2, -1)--(6.8, -1));
draw((7.2, -1)--(8.8, -1), target);
draw((9.2, -1)--(10.8, -1));
draw((11.2, -1)--(12.8, -1));
draw((13.2, -1)--(14.8, -1));
draw((15.2, -1)--(16.8, -1));

pen tube = black + linewidth(2);
draw((7.2, 9)--(7.2, 7.8)--(8.8, 7.8)--(8.8, 9), tube);

filldraw(Circle((8, 8.5), 0.6), blue);
[/asy]
A) \frac{35}{128}
B) \frac{34}{128}

Answer this question with the single letter for the correct answer only. Beth rolls a fair six-sided die. If she rolls a prime number, she wins 1 dollar, but if she rolls a composite number, she loses 1 dollar. If she rolls 1 nothing happens. What is the expected value of the amount of money Beth will win if she rolls the die once? Express your answer as a common fraction.
A) \frac{0}{6}
B) \frac{1}{6}

Answer this question with the single letter for the correct answer only. How many different rectangles are in the figure? [asy]
defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
draw((0,0)--(0,5)--(8,5)--(8,0)--cycle);
draw((0,3)--(8,3));
draw((6,5)--(6,0));
[/asy]
A) 11
B) 9

Answer this question with the single letter for the correct answer only. Let $a_1,$ $a_2,$ $\dots,$ $a_{12}$ be real numbers such that $a_1 + a_2 + \dots + a_{12} = 1.$  Find the minimum value of
\[a_1^2 + a_2^2 + \dots + a_{12}^2.\]
A) \frac{1}{12}
B) \frac{-1}{12}

Answer this question with the single letter for the correct answer only. Let $\mathbb{Q}^+$ denote the set of positive rational numbers.  Let $f : \mathbb{Q}^+ \to \mathbb{Q}^+$ be a function such that
\[f \left( x + \frac{y}{x} \right) = f(x) + \frac{f(y)}{f(x)} + 2y\]for all $x,$ $y \in \mathbb{Q}^+.$

Find all possible values of $f \left( \frac{1}{3} \right).$  Enter all the possible values, separated by commas.
A) \frac{1}{9}
B) \frac{3}{9}

Answer this question with the single letter for the correct answer only. Paul and Jesse each choose a number at random from the first six primes. What is the probability that the sum of the numbers they choose is even?
A) \frac{13}{18}
B) \frac{12}{18}

Answer this question with the single letter for the correct answer only. The complex numbers $\alpha_1, \alpha_2, \alpha_3$, and $\alpha_4$ are the four distinct roots of the equation $x^4+2x^3+2=0$. Determine the unordered set \[
\{\alpha_1\alpha_2 + \alpha_3\alpha_4, \alpha_1\alpha_3 + \alpha_2\alpha_4, \alpha_1\alpha_4 + \alpha_2\alpha_3\}.
\]
A) \{1\pm\sqrt{7},-2\}
B) \{1\pm\sqrt{5},-2\}

Answer this question with the single letter for the correct answer only. The letters C, O, U, N and T are randomly placed around a circle. One such arrangement is shown here. If we always start with the C and continue to read the rest of the letters in order clockwise, in how many different orders can the letters appear?

[asy]
draw(circle((0,0),1),dashed);
label("U",dir(90));
label("C",dir(90+360/5));
label("O",dir(90+2*360/5));
label("N",dir(90+3*360/5));
label("T",dir(90+4*360/5));
[/asy]
A) 24
B) 22
